<!-- Q1(b): Google Sheets -->
<div id="q1b">
<div class="qblock"><div class="qnum">Q1(b)</div><div><div class="qtitle">Google Sheets — Cloud Storage Cost Comparison</div><div class="qsub">4 cloud services · formulas for Storage Cost · Discount · Net Cost</div></div><span class="mbadge m4">3 Marks</span></div>
<div class="sec">📖 Objective</div>
<div class="understand"><div class="ul">What to do</div><p>Create a Google Sheets spreadsheet comparing cloud storage costs of 4 cloud services. Apply the given formulas for Storage Cost, Discount (based on thresholds), and Net Cost using IF conditions.</p></div>
<div class="sec">🔷 Spreadsheet Data &amp; Formulas</div>
<div class="ans-card"><div class="ans-head"><span>Google Sheets — Cloud Storage Cost Calculator</span></div>
<div class="ans-body">
<p><strong>Spreadsheet Structure (enter this data in Google Sheets):</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Cloud Service</th><th>Web Address</th><th>Space (GB)</th><th>Cost/GB (₹)</th><th>Storage Cost (₹)</th><th>Discount (₹)</th><th>Net Cost (₹)</th></tr>
<tr><td>Amazon S3</td><td>aws.amazon.com/s3</td><td>500</td><td>180</td><td>=C2*D2</td><td>=IF(E2&lt;100000,0,IF(E2&lt;500000,E2*0.10,E2*0.25))</td><td>=E2-F2</td></tr>
<tr><td>Google Cloud</td><td>cloud.google.com</td><td>1000</td><td>160</td><td>=C3*D3</td><td>=IF(E3&lt;100000,0,IF(E3&lt;500000,E3*0.10,E3*0.25))</td><td>=E3-F3</td></tr>
<tr><td>Microsoft Azure</td><td>azure.microsoft.com</td><td>2000</td><td>175</td><td>=C4*D4</td><td>=IF(E4&lt;100000,0,IF(E4&lt;500000,E4*0.10,E4*0.25))</td><td>=E4-F4</td></tr>
<tr><td>IBM Cloud</td><td>ibm.com/cloud</td><td>3000</td><td>190</td><td>=C5*D5</td><td>=IF(E5&lt;100000,0,IF(E5&lt;500000,E5*0.10,E5*0.25))</td><td>=E5-F5</td></tr>
</table>
<p><strong>Computed Output Values:</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Cloud Service</th><th>Space (GB)</th><th>Cost/GB (₹)</th><th>Storage Cost (₹)</th><th>Discount (₹)</th><th>Net Cost (₹)</th></tr>
<tr><td>Amazon S3</td><td>500</td><td>180</td><td>90,000</td><td>0 (below 1L)</td><td>90,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Google Cloud</td><td>1000</td><td>160</td><td>1,60,000</td><td>16,000 (10%)</td><td>1,44,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Microsoft Azure</td><td>2000</td><td>175</td><td>3,50,000</td><td>35,000 (10%)</td><td>3,15,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>IBM Cloud</td><td>3000</td><td>190</td><td>5,70,000</td><td>1,42,500 (25%)</td><td>4,27,500</td></tr>
</table>
<p><strong>Discount Logic (IF Formula):</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Storage Cost &lt; ₹1,00,000 → Discount = 0</li>
<li>₹1,00,000 ≤ Storage Cost &lt; ₹5,00,000 → Discount = 10% of Storage Cost</li>
<li>Storage Cost ≥ ₹5,00,000 → Discount = 25% of Storage Cost</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Result:</strong> Google Sheets spreadsheet successfully created with 4 cloud services, cost comparison formulas, and discount logic. IBM Cloud offers the best discount at 25% for large storage (5.7 lakh+ cost).</p>
